<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Profiler Home tab</b></p><p>The Profiler tool window (<span class="shortcut">View | Tool Windows | Profiler</span>) provides an overview of the running processes and recent snapshots. Use it to start profiling, monitor live performance metrics, or get a memory or thread dump for a selected process.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/ij-recent-snapshots.png" alt="Recent Snapshots on the Profiler home tab" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p><p>If you are new to profiling, we recommend following <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/tutorial-get-started-with-profiling.html">this tutorial</a>, which gets you started on profiling basics in IntelliJ IDEA.</p></body></html>